# Cross-Platform Consistency

The web app (`frontend/`) and mobile app (`mobile/`) are separate codebases that share a backend and common utilities. When the user requests a feature or fix, always clarify scope.

## Before Implementing

When a feature request could apply to both platforms, ask:
- "Should this apply to the web app, the mobile app, or both?"
- "Should the behavior be consistent between web and mobile?"

Do NOT assume "mobile" means the responsive web view — this project has a dedicated Expo/React Native app in `mobile/`.

## Shared Code

When implementing the same feature on both platforms, extract shared logic into `common/src/` where possible:
- HTML/CSS generation (e.g., `common/src/emailHtmlStyles.ts`)
- Type definitions and constants
- Business logic that doesn't depend on platform APIs

## Platform Differences

Each platform has its own patterns — don't copy web patterns into mobile or vice versa:

| Concern | Web (`frontend/`) | Mobile (`mobile/`) |
|---------|-------------------|-------------------|
| GraphQL | Apollo hooks or `fetch()` with codegen types | `apolloClient.query()` / `.mutate()` |
| Auth tokens | `supabase.auth.getSession()` | `secureGet(STORAGE_KEYS.AUTH_TOKEN)` |
| Styling | styled-components / `.wrappers.ts` | `StyleSheet.create()` + theme constants |
| Navigation | React Router (`useNavigate`) | React Navigation (props callbacks) |
| State | React context / Zustand | Zustand stores |
| File download | Blob URL + anchor click | `expo-file-system` + `expo-sharing` |
